sub_fields.label: First Card Open?
sub_fields.name: first_card_open
sub_fields.instructions: Select True to have the first card open at page load.

sub_fields.label: Always Open?
sub_fields.name: always_open
sub_fields.instructions: Always Open keeps cards open when opening another.

sub_fields.label: Flush Accordion?
sub_fields.name: flush_accordion
sub_fields.instructions: Flush Accordion removes some borders and rounded corners.

sub_fields.label: Autoplay?
sub_fields.name: autoplay
sub_fields.instructions: Will slides autoplay without user interaction?

sub_fields.label: Cross-fade?
sub_fields.name: cross_fade
sub_fields.instructions: Will slides fade instead of sliding?

sub_fields.label: Fill Viewport?
sub_fields.name: fill_viewport
sub_fields.instructions: Will the Carousel fill the viewport?

sub_fields.label: Video URL
sub_fields.name: video_url
sub_fields.instructions: Copy/Paste the page URL you want to embed, the field will capture the video in an iframe.

sub_fields.label: Aspect Ratio
sub_fields.name: aspect_ratio
sub_fields.instructions: Choose the aspect ratio for the embedded video, this will help to maintain the ratio when changing screen size.

sub_fields.label: Selected Posts
sub_fields.name: selected_posts
sub_fields.instructions: Selected a group of Posts to display.

sub_fields.label: Selected Posts
sub_fields.name: selected_posts
sub_fields.instructions: Select a group of posts to display. Similar to Post Objects, the key differences are in the field options when setting it tup.

sub_fields.label: Video Source
sub_fields.name: video_source
sub_fields.instructions: Choose the source of the video.

sub_fields.label: Local Video
sub_fields.name: local_video
sub_fields.instructions: Choose a video file from the Media Library.

sub_fields.label: Hosted Video
sub_fields.name: hosted_video
sub_fields.instructions: Enter the url of video hosted online, e.g. uploaded via FTP but not in the media library.

sub_fields.label: Embeded Video
sub_fields.name: embeded_video
sub_fields.instructions:
Enter the url for an embedded video, e.g. a video hosted on YouTube/Vimeo.

Parameters to convert the video to a background are added automatically.

sub_fields.label: Inline Video?
sub_fields.name: inline_video
sub_fields.instructions: An inline video has controls and can be interacted with by the user.
